UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407687900467
AB  - A sample of 58 countries for the period 1969–1978 is analyzed in order to determine the role of prices and various forms of public inputs on agricultural supply and some factor demand. The within-country analysis provides estimates of weak short-run supply elasticities. The main determinants of output, both within country and across countries are variables representing infrastructures and a measure of comprehensive capital. The results are evaluated within a theoretical framework.
